Results

Load our package jm5 and separate AIDS dataset to longitudinal dataset and survival dataset

Define our longitudinal formula and survival formula, and separate datasets

l.formula <- CD4 ~ obstime + drug + prevOI + AZT
s.formula <- Surv(Time, death) ~ drug
dat <- JM::aids
l <- jm_filter(l.formula, s.formula, dat, ID = dat$patient)
long.dat <- l[[1]]
surv.dat <- l[[2]]

Summary statistics for AIDS dataset

Variable Description
ID Patients identifier (1-467)
Time The time to death or censoring
death 0 for censoring, 1 for death
CD4 The CD4 cells count
obstime The time points at which the CD4 cells count was recorded (0, 2, 6, 12, 18)
drug ddI (1) for didanosine, ddC (0) for zalcitabine
prevOI AIDS (1) for previous opportunistic infection, noAIDS (0) for no previous infection
AZT failure (1) for AZT failure, intolerance (0) for AZT intolerance
gender 1 for male, 0 for female
